{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-details-js","path":"/blog/redesigning-my-personal-website","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>After a few years of my personal website's existence I decided it was time to give it an update and I went ahead and did that.</p>\n<p>This is how the website looked before and after the update.</p>\n<p>My website before the update.\r\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 200px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1bfe2b950572a5c8a7f4f09e3482b3a2/78797/portfolio-site-old.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 216%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Old website\"\n        title=\"Old website\"\n        src=\"/static/1bfe2b950572a5c8a7f4f09e3482b3a2/772e8/portfolio-site-old.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1bfe2b950572a5c8a7f4f09e3482b3a2/a1812/portfolio-site-old.png 50w,\n/static/1bfe2b950572a5c8a7f4f09e3482b3a2/7e516/portfolio-site-old.png 100w,\n/static/1bfe2b950572a5c8a7f4f09e3482b3a2/772e8/portfolio-site-old.png 200w,\n/static/1bfe2b950572a5c8a7f4f09e3482b3a2/5a46d/portfolio-site-old.png 300w,\n/static/1bfe2b950572a5c8a7f4f09e3482b3a2/e17e5/portfolio-site-old.png 400w,\n/static/1bfe2b950572a5c8a7f4f09e3482b3a2/78797/portfolio-site-old.png 1125w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>My website after the update.\r\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 200px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d2a9bae8d16bf6f9a6425d0e4885de40/78797/portfolio-site-new.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 216%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"New website\"\n        title=\"New website\"\n        src=\"/static/d2a9bae8d16bf6f9a6425d0e4885de40/772e8/portfolio-site-new.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d2a9bae8d16bf6f9a6425d0e4885de40/a1812/portfolio-site-new.png 50w,\n/static/d2a9bae8d16bf6f9a6425d0e4885de40/7e516/portfolio-site-new.png 100w,\n/static/d2a9bae8d16bf6f9a6425d0e4885de40/772e8/portfolio-site-new.png 200w,\n/static/d2a9bae8d16bf6f9a6425d0e4885de40/5a46d/portfolio-site-new.png 300w,\n/static/d2a9bae8d16bf6f9a6425d0e4885de40/e17e5/portfolio-site-new.png 400w,\n/static/d2a9bae8d16bf6f9a6425d0e4885de40/78797/portfolio-site-new.png 1125w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The changes I made to the new website are as follows.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Booting out bootstrap</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Added blog functionality</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Light mode and dark mode themes</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Simplified design</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p>My reasons for the above are as follows</p>\n<h3>Booting out bootstrap</h3>\n<p>On the old website I was using bootstrap, particularly it's grid system and the mobile first navbar. I feel like the parts of bootstrap I was using on the site were too small to justify adding an entire bootsrap library on this new site, so I rather rewrote the parts I used by using plain css.</p>\n<h3>Added blog functionality</h3>\n<p>On the new website I also wanted to add a blog, so I chose <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/\">gatsby js</a> in order to do that. The website was previously a plain JS, HTML &#x26; CSS project.</p>\n<h3>Light mode and dark mode themes</h3>\n<p>I have added a light and a dark theme, the website will adapt and match the theme you are using on your device (computer or mobile).</p>\n<h3>Simplified design</h3>\n<p>I'm not a design expert but on this new website I tried to use less font and I decided to drop the background imagery I was using.</p>\n<p>That's all for now see you on the next post.</p>","frontmatter":{"slug":"redesigning-my-personal-website","title":"Redesigning my Personal Website ðŸ–ŒðŸŽ¨","author":"Teboho","date":"2021-08-14T00:00:00.000Z","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5151515151515151,"src":"/static/39de46b9f280ed6adeba397b101fae09/14b42/photo-1517697471339-4aa32003c11a.jpg","srcSet":"/static/39de46b9f280ed6adeba397b101fae09/f836f/photo-1517697471339-4aa32003c11a.jpg 200w,\n/static/39de46b9f280ed6adeba397b101fae09/2244e/photo-1517697471339-4aa32003c11a.jpg 400w,\n/static/39de46b9f280ed6adeba397b101fae09/14b42/photo-1517697471339-4aa32003c11a.jpg 800w,\n/static/39de46b9f280ed6adeba397b101fae09/47498/photo-1517697471339-4aa32003c11a.jpg 1200w,\n/static/39de46b9f280ed6adeba397b101fae09/0e329/photo-1517697471339-4aa32003c11a.jpg 1600w,\n/static/39de46b9f280ed6adeba397b101fae09/808c6/photo-1517697471339-4aa32003c11a.jpg 1955w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"redesigning-my-personal-website"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}